# ============================================================================
# _modbus_proxy — zsh completion for **modbus_proxy** —
#                  fluffware/modbus_proxy, the **Modbus TCP
#                  aggregator** that lets multiple Modbus TCP
#                  client applications share access to a single
#                  upstream Modbus device (whether that upstream
#                  device is a Modbus TCP server on the network or
#                  a Modbus RTU device behind a serial port).
#                  Solves the canonical "my PLC only accepts one
#                  Modbus TCP client at a time" problem by
#                  multiplexing requests + responses by Modbus
#                  Application Header transaction-ID, with built-
#                  in inter-frame request delay enforcement for
#                  Modbus RTU's strict timing requirements.  Rust=
#                  173 OPENING leg of new Axis 118 (Modbus / MOD-
#                  BUS Application Protocol over TCP and RTU) via
#                  the canonical async Rust Modbus library
#                  **slowtec/tokio-modbus**.
